+## Question 6: Hierarchical Page Tables
+
+Goal: given two L1 page-table roots `PTA` and `PTB`, share identical L2 subtrees so total page-table memory decreases, while translations remain unchanged.
+
+Assumptions from prompt:
+- 32-bit VA: `L1 index (10 bits) | L2 index (10 bits) | offset (12 bits)`.
+- Each L1 table has 1024 entries; each L2 table has 1024 PTEs.
+- L2 PTE format is the Yalnix/RCS421 format.
+- We may directly dereference addresses for this question.
+
+```text
+const int L1_ENTRIES = 1024;
+const int L2_ENTRIES = 1024;
+
+// Returns pointer to the L2 table referenced by an L1 PTE.
+// (Conceptually: pfn -> address; exact bit extraction follows Yalnix PTE format.)
+L2Table *L2PtrFromL1PTE(PTE l1e) {
+    pfn = EXTRACT_PFN(l1e);
+    return (L2Table *)(pfn << 12);
+}
+
+bool EqualL2(L2Table *a, L2Table *b) {
+    for (int k = 0; k < L2_ENTRIES; k++) {
+        if (a->pte[k] != b->pte[k]) return false;
+    }
+    return true;
+}
+
+// Input: pointers to two L1 roots (modified in place)
+procedure ShareIdenticalSubtrees(L1Table *PTA, L1Table *PTB) {
+    // List of canonical L2 tables already kept
+    list<L2Table *> canonical;
+
+    // Helper: process one L1 table entry and deduplicate its L2 target
+    procedure ProcessOneEntry(L1Table *root, int i) {
+        PTE l1e = root->pte[i];
+        if (!VALID(l1e)) return;                    // no subtree at this slot
+
+        L2Table *cur = L2PtrFromL1PTE(l1e);
+
+        // Find previously seen identical L2 table
+        for each L2Table *rep in canonical {
+            if (EqualL2(cur, rep)) {
+                // Rewrite this L1 entry to point to representative subtree
+                root->pte[i] = MAKE_L1_PTE_FROM_ADDR(rep, l1e);
+
+                // Current subtree now redundant (no longer referenced by this entry)
+                // In full OS code, free only when refcount reaches 0.
+                DecrementRefcountAndFreeIfZero(cur);
+                return;
+            }
+        }
+
+        // No match: keep this as a new representative
+        canonical.push_back(cur);
+    }
+
+    // Deduplicate across both trees (and within each tree)
+    for (int i = 0; i < L1_ENTRIES; i++) ProcessOneEntry(PTA, i);
+    for (int i = 0; i < L1_ENTRIES; i++) ProcessOneEntry(PTB, i);
+}
+```
+
+How this accesses/modifies tables in detail:
+1. For each valid L1 entry in each root, read its PFN/address and dereference that L2 table.
+2. Compare all 1024 L2 PTEs against previously accepted canonical L2 tables.
+3. If a byte-for-byte-equal L2 table exists, rewrite the current parent L1 PTE so it points to that representative L2 table.
+4. Free redundant L2 memory only when no parent still references it (refcount check).
+5. If no equal table exists, keep current one as canonical.
+
+Correctness argument:
+- Rewriting occurs only when two L2 tables are identical in every entry, so every VPN covered by that L1 slot maps exactly as before.
+- Therefore both processes' address translation behavior remains unchanged, while duplicate L2 physical memory is eliminated.
